OL,3,CMarketing of iPlayer at the expense
OL,4,Cof BBC One
OL,6,FIf you heard radio trails yesterday
OL,7,Fmorning for last night's episode of
OL,8,FDoctor Who one key phrase was
OL,9,Fmissing: "Tonight at 6.30 on BBC
OL,10,FOne." Instead the iPlayer was
OL,11,Fpromoted.
OL,13,FFor anyone living in the parallel
OL,14,Funiverse where BBC One is just a
OL,15,Flegacy service, the overnight ratings
OL,16,Fwill have been a shock. An impressive
OL,17,F5.1m people tuned in to watch.
