OL,3,CMarketing of iPlayer at the expense
OL,4,Cof BBC One
OL,6,FThere is no doubt, of course, that
OL,7,Fmany people enjoy watching box sets.
OL,8,FBut I would suggest the habit of
OL,9,Fdropping entire series on the iPlayer
OL,10,Fahead of screenings on a linear
OL,11,Fservice can often be
OL,12,Fcounterproductive.
OL,14,FWhat's wrong with saying "new
OL,15,Fepisodes drop every Sunday at nine"?
OL,16,FOver the space of a few weeks the box
OL,17,Fset will then build up.
OL,19,FThere can even be compromises.
